    <h1>Old online store: BitPay</h1><div id="preamble">
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="admonitionblock important">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-important" title="Important"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Integration only for Callisto online stores</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>This page only contains instructions for integrating <strong>BitPay</strong> in Callisto online stores. The following instructions are not valid for Ceres stores!</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>BitPay is a leading payment service provider specialising in the peer-to-peer virtual currency Bitcoin. BitPay provides for instantaneous transactions from anywhere in the world with no risk of fraud or chargebacks.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="10">1. Important notes</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>This chapter provides you with important information about integrating the payment provider in plentymarkets.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph subhead">
<p>Payment process</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Once the order has been placed, the customer will receive a message asking them to click on a link and make the payment. The customer will be forwarded to the BitPay website after having clicked on the link. The customer has to enter the necessary data for the payment. Once the customer has entered and confirmed the data, they will be forwarded to the order confirmation page.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph subhead">
<p>Manual payment import</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>BitPay payments will not be automatically imported into plentymarkets. BitPay payments must be <a href="/en/payment/managing-payments#40">booked manually</a>.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="20">2. Registering with BitPay</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You need to register with BitPay before you can set up the payment method in plentymarkets. <a href="https://bitpay.com/start" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Contact</a> the payment provider in order to complete the registration process. You will then receive the necessary information as well as the access data that you need for the configuration in plentymarkets.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="30">3. Setting up BitPay for Callisto</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Proceed as described below to set up the interface to BitPay for your Callisto online store in plentymarkets.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Setting up the interface to BitPay:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Setup » Orders » Payment » Methods</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Place a check mark next to the setting <strong>Also show inactive</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Open the folder <strong>International</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>BitPay</strong>.<br>
→ The <strong>Settings</strong> tab will open.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>Interface</strong> tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Expand the client.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Carry out the settings as desired. Pay attention to the information given in <a href="#table-setup-bitpay-interface">Table 1</a>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
