</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="40">4. Activating the payment method</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Set up and activate the BitPay <a href="/en/payment/managing-payment-methods#20">payment method</a> in the <strong>Settings</strong> tab of the payment method. In addition, check the settings for <strong>Permitted payment methods</strong> in the <a href="/en/payment/managing-payment-methods#30">customer classes</a> and for <strong>Blocked payment methods</strong> in the <a href="/en/fulfilment/preparing-the-shipment#1000">shipping profiles</a>.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="50">5. Viewing the API log</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In the rare case that an error occurs during data transmission, you will find details about the corresponding error in the API Log. Depending on the type of error, the payment may be booked in BitPay but may not be verified in plentymarkets. This will cause an erroneous booking in plentymarkets.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Viewing the API log:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Data » API log » Tab: API log</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select a format from the drop-down list <strong>Process</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select a <strong>Date</strong> if you only want to see entries for a specific day.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Search</strong> to carry out the search.<br>
→ The processes will be displayed.</p>
</li>
</ol>
